value.name: List of Deutsche Bahn AG locomotives and railbuses - Wikipedia
value.snippet: The classes are numbered according to the locomotive classification of the Deutsche Bundesbahn, which had been adopted by Deutsche Bahn in 1994. Since 2007, classifications for all German railway companies are centrally issued by the Federal Railway Office in line with UIC classification rules .

value.name: List of Deutsche Bundesbahn locomotives and railbuses
value.snippet: For vehicles of the Deutsche Bahn see the List of DBAG locomotives and railbuses . Steam locomotive classes are arranged in accordance with the DRG classification system; electric and diesel locomotives, railbuses and works vehicles are listed in accordance with the DB classification scheme.

value.name: DB locomotive classification - Wikipedia
value.snippet: When UIC introduced a new classification system that could be processed by the computers of the late 1960s, DB did a major modification of their system, effective 1 January 1968. This system is still in use and now includes the engines of the former GDR railways as well.

value.name: LHB prototype carriages - Wikipedia
value.snippet: DB considered the LHB prototypes and modified a number of them into InterCity carriages so that two push-pull trains became available. The two driving trailers Bnrzf 732 retained their open coach seating and were rebuilt into 1st class carriages Azf 209 .

value.name: DB class 732 (1989) - DB-Baureihe 732 (1989)
value.snippet: The special vehicle of the DB series 732 belonged to the Hamburg S-Bahn and was equipped with a device to keep the conductor rails free from icing. It was used as a replacement for the vehicles of the 730/731 series. In 2001 the single vehicle was taken out of service and later scrapped.
